readme: ## trim-left-x (a.k.a trimStart in ES2019) This method removes whitespace from the start of a string. ### `module.exports(string)` number ### `trim-left-x` string This method removes whitespace from the left end of a string. (ES2019) **Kind**: static property of [trim-left-x](#module_trim-left-x) **Returns**: string - The left trimmed string. **Throws**: - TypeError If string is null or undefined or not coercible. | Param | Type | Description | | ------ | ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | | string | string | The string to trim the left end whitespace from. | **Example** ```js import trimStart from 'trim-left-x'; console.log(trimStart(' \t\na \t\n') === 'a \t\n'); // true ```
